{
  "video_id": "p8JGQ23PTWg",
  "title": "Walter Stahel: Circular Economy",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 313.0,
      "end_time": 5532.0,
      "text": "Whether clothing, furniture, electronics, vehicles, or buildings,"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 6320.0,
      "end_time": 10962.0,
      "text": "we surround ourselves with objects that we use only for a limited time."
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 13931.0,
      "end_time": 19310.0,
      "text": "The resources which are extracted from planet Earth to make these objects"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 19310.0,
      "end_time": 22811.0,
      "text": "are used once or twice and then dumped."
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 27282.0,
      "end_time": 32409.0,
      "text": "Yet, the resources on our planet are non-renewable and finite,"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 32409.0,
      "end_time": 37322.0,
      "text": "except for rainfall, sunlight, biomass, animals, and people."
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 38613.0,
      "end_time": 42714.0,
      "text": "And our global commons have become waste dumps."
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 44742.0,
      "end_time": 50403.0,
      "text": "Within 60 years, we have filled the oceans with millions of low-tech plastic objects"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 50403.0,
      "end_time": 54240.0,
      "text": "and space with thousands of high-tech objects."
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 56563.0,
      "end_time": 60682.0,
      "text": "So, the present industrial economy is not compatible"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 60682.0,
      "end_time": 65993.0,
      "text": "with the natural resources and waste dumps available on planet Earth."
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 69103.0,
      "end_time": 72750.0,
      "text": "More of the same is no business model for success."
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 72751.0,
      "end_time": 76410.0,
      "text": "We need to create higher standards of living"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 76410.0,
      "end_time": 78933.0,
      "text": "from a more intelligent resource use."
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 80782.0,
      "end_time": 82582.0,
      "text": "More from less."
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 84112.0,
      "end_time": 87161.0,
      "text": "I have an idea how to do it."
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 87162.0,
      "end_time": 88772.0,
      "text": "Circularity."
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 89584.0,
      "end_time": 93243.0,
      "text": "♪ (dramatic music) ♪"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 93243.0,
      "end_time": 95673.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s great, you&#39;ll love it."
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 102151.0,
      "end_time": 103832.0,
      "text": "Circularity."
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 103832.0,
      "end_time": 105770.0,
      "text": "That is how nature works."
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 105771.0,
      "end_time": 109912.0,
      "text": "Water, biomass, CO2, seasons."
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 109912.0,
      "end_time": 111952.0,
      "text": "Nature works in cycles."
    }
  ]
